F>(8/31/01 11:20:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stonebrunt quest + Trivial loot code = lame as hell.</span><hr size=1> I am all for the trivial looting code since it affects too many appropriate leveled players that cannot get loot since a high level is farming a whole groups area, see lguk, sola.<br>
<br>
Sadly the no-drop system does not work well. It prevents people from farming but also has so bad side effects, such as new quest items being awarded to the wrong class or vulchers like in icewell with royal velium having better gear than players that fought hard and well in the planes.<br>
<br>
Verants just has to walk a finer line at what items should be dropping in areas that are restricted by higher levels and when they make an mistake, discontinue an item's drop.<br>
<br>
Oh, I would also like an item that snares, but I am not up for doing a lowbee quest for hours to have 4 charges of snare and mowing through an area for level 20-30s. <br>
<br>
I am willing to pay the price of not getting an item if this allows level appropriate players from having a zone to exp grind/explore and loot items without hoping that not everything is farmed by some super high levels.<br>
<br>
<br>
