</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utuazenthulebane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuazen Thulebane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/31/01 11:51:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stonebrunt quest + Trivial loot code = lame as hell.</span><hr size=1> Threads like this always crack me up. Get this idea in your heads, Verant does not like spoiler sites. They've said it time and time again and then they finally started doing something about it. Bottom line is that if you didn't already know that the snare item (for example) was in the zone, you can't get mad about missing out on it. <br>
<br>
I'm all for the trivial code. Now I will say that if someone gives you a quest you should be able to complete it. If you're too high level to complete the quest because of TLC you should be told so by the quest giver so you don't waste any of your time. <br>
<br>
Now the reason people go to LOIO is its widely regarded as great xp and its easy to get a group there. Same reason folks go to OT, Dreadlands, Seb, Guk, KC, etc. Some folks think that people will only go to a zone if its got good loot, but the fact is thats not the case at all. People only go to a zone if there's a good chance they will get a group there. Hence 120 dumbasses in LOIO when there are places with better xp and loot for that level range they could be at. This is the same reason folks have full groups camping the orcs in East commons/N.Ro, when they could take that same group to a low level dungeon and just rack in the xp and loot. Its not EQ thats fucked up, its the players. <br>
<br>
